28/05/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The cabinet on Thursday (27 May) approved a long-term defence programme and prioritised 11 investment projects to modernise the army.
The plan envisions investments of 767m euros for repair and purchase of new equipment through 2010.
Now that it is a full NATO member, Bulgaria must continue streamlining equipment and personnel.
Also Thursday, Sofia began hosting a two-day meeting of the Committee on Economic Affairs and Development of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe.
(BTA, BNT, Mediapool, Dnevnik, bTV - 27/05/04)
